parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents.
Failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Misrepresentation of airbag condition can lead to buyers purchasing vehicles with faulty or deployed airbags, which can compromise safety.
symptoms: Airbags are deployed but not replaced

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Sludge Buildup
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure due to sludge buildup can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs, potential accidents, and strandings.
Spark plug failure can cause engine misfires, loss of engine power, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: Spark plugs blow out of the hole

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, surrounding property, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
Transmission failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and strandings.
Fuel pump failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents.
Electrical and relay problems can cause a range of issues, including engine failure, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
Engine knocking or unusual noises can be indicative of underlying engine problems, potentially leading to engine failure.
The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the check engine warning light illuminates
the fuel gauge does not indicate the accurate amount of fuel in the vehicle
and the speed control warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle catching on fire can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire while parked or in operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to lose speed control, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control switch fails to activate
and the vehicle speed cruise control does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off while in motion, leading to accidents or loss of control, and potentially causing fires.
symptoms: automatic lights and airbag lights malfunction
bright lights turn on by themselves
and the vehicle shuts off while moving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Leakage and Electrical System Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage can cause corrosion of the electrical system, leading to faulty wiring and electrical system failures, which can cause accidents or fires.
The malfunction of the airbag and seatbelt system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: and seatbelt fails to work properly.
